   <!-- ws-10-11-22: Listed as a unitary text although part of a larger set-->
      
         <text>
            <body>
               <div type='page' n='77'><!-- ws:10-11-22: Assuming there are 365 pages, 77 corresponds with March 17th -->
                  <!-- ws:10-11-22: Thought about putting the copyright in it's own div element, but went against it because it is still part of the page-->
                  <p rend='align(center)'>COPYRIGHT 1909, BY<lb/>
                     FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.<lb/>
                     NEW BRITAIN, CONN.<lb/>
                  </p>
                  <p rend='align(left)'>
                     <date when='1909-03-17'><emph>M</emph>ARCH 17, 1909.
                     WEDNESDAY
                     <persName>St. Patrick</persName>'s Day</date>
                  </p>
                  <figure>
                     <figDesc>Two green three-leaf clovers are stamped onto the page alsong with two snakes drawn in black pen.</figDesc>   
                  </figure>
                  <p>
                     <lg type='stanza'> <!-- ws-10-11-22: Unsure how to make it clear that some letters are capitalized without marking every single instance -->
                        <l><persName>St. Patrick</persName> was a <unclear reason="misspelling">useful</unclear> saint</l>
                        <l>He frightened all the snakes away-</l>
                        <l>I wish he'd try his art on <emph rend="underline">smoke</emph></l>
                        <figure><!-- ws-10-11-22: The stamp can be marked as being between the two lines -->
                           <figDesc>A single green three-leaf clover stamp.</figDesc>
                        </figure>
                        <l>Around the Hammermill some day !</l>
                     </lg>
                  </p>
                  <figure> <!-- ws-10-11-22: While I'm positive it's optional, the placement of figures on a page would be an interesting problem to tackle -->
                     <figDesc>A single green three-leaf clover stamp on the left of the page, accompagnied by a sketch of the Hammermill building billowing smoke in black on the right side of the page.</figDesc>
                  </figure>
                  <p>
                     <hi rend='red-pen'>The Hammermill really <emph rend='underline'><unclear reason="illegible">does</unclear> smoke!</emph></hi> 
                  </p>
               </div>
            </body>
         </text>
